Model Summary

Fit across folds by factor model

Count of folds out of 10 with flagged problems

Notes:
‘common structure’ is the number of folds the EFA identified the most common structure. Thus, “common structure” will be 10 when the same structure was identified in every fold and < 10 when multiple factor structures were identified. The most common structure was used in the CFA. See Appendix for all structures.
‘improper solution’ is the number of folds with non-convergence or a non-positive definite matrix.
‘high factor correlation’ threshold set to 0.9.
‘low scale reliability’ threshold set to 0.6 with \(\omega_h\).
‘low loading’ threshold set to 0.3.
blanks = not applicable
